Aim-listed IronRidge Resources has appointed Amanda Harsas as full time CFO with immediate effect. She is a senior finance executive with over 20 years’ experience in strategic finance, business transformation, commercial finance, customer and supplier negotiations and capital management. She has broad experience across several sectors including healthcare, insurance, retail and professional services. Harsas is a chartered accountant, holds a Bachelor of Business degree and has international experience in Asia, Europe and the US. “IronRidge continues to strengthen its management team as it makes its transition from explorer to developer. We are delighted Amanda is joining us in this important role and at such a pivotal time in the company’s history,” says IronRidge chairperson Neil Herbert.